1�This is Windurst Walls, the centermost of the four districts that make up the Federation of Windurst. It is also the political centaru of Windurst.
1�If you need directions to make your way around Windurst Walls, go ask Jack of Diamonds in the open area down thattaru way.
1�You cannotaru accept more than one mission at a time. Please completaru your current mission before applying for the next.
1�Letaru me see...The missions you are able to receive...

1�Which mission will you accept?The Horutoto Ruins Experiment.The Heart of the Matter.The Price of Peace.Lost for Words.A Testing Time.The Three Kingdoms.Mission 2-3-1A.Mission 2-3-1B.Mission 2-3-2A.Mission 2-3-2B.To Each His Own Right.Written in the Stars.A New Journey.Magicite.The Final Seal.The Shadow Awaits.Full Moon Fountain.Saintly Invitation.The Sixth Ministry.Awakening of the Gods.Vain.The Jester Who'd Be King.Doll of the Dead.Moon Reading.Dummy11.Dummy12.Dummy13.Dummy14.Dummy15.Dummy16.Dummy17.Decline mission.
1�Accept this mission?Yes.No.
1�Know much aboutaru gatehouses?No, I don'taru.Yes, enough.
1�Receive a mission?Acceptaru.Decline.
1�...Looks like he's preoccupied.So, erm, hey Pakke-Pokke...! Give the newcomer a mission appropriatarue for ?[his/her] rank, please.
1�Head over to the Orastery building in Port Windurst and ask the minister there for your mission details.

1�Oh, and just in case you didn'taru know...The Orastery is one of the five ministries of Windurst. It is also known as the ??Mage Academy,?? as itaru is the place where they train the most powerful magic users to help serve the Federation.
1�Well done!We'll allocatarue you rank points according to our evaluation of your mission. Come back again soon and try your hand ataru another mission.
1�Well done!We'll allocatarue you rank points according to our evaluation of your mission. Come back again soon and try your hand ataru another mission.
1�Acceptaru this mission?Acceptaru.Decline.
1�Go ask the staff who work ataru the Manustery's Cardian workshop in Windurst Woods for the details of your mission.

1�To getaru to Windurst Woods from here, just cross the bridge and head south. Keep heading south pastaru the auction house and across the bridge there. I recommend you keep checking your map so as not to getaru lost.
1�Head over to the Rhinostery in Windurst Waters and pick up the food offerings for the Yagudo. Then go deliver them to Giddeus.
1�Windurst Waters is west of where we stand in Windurst Walls. The quickestaru way to get there is to cross the bridge nextaru to Koru-Moru's manor.
1�Good, good...Thataru seemed to go withoutaru a hitch this time.
1�Oh, and congratarulations!Now thataru you've cleared three missions, you are entitled to advance to rank two!

1�Before I can issue you another mission, we require you to participate in the conquest campaign for a while in order to amass some rank points. Speak to the guard in charge of conquests for further details.
1�Let's keep working together to protectaru Windurst's justaruice, libertaruy, and love!
1�Acceptaru this mission?Acceptaru.Decline.
1�The Library of Magic thataru the Optistery runs is west of here, in Windurst Waters. To find outaru what your mission involves, speak to the Minister of the Optistery in the library there.
1�You remember how to getaru to Windurst Waters, rightaru? Head west and cross the bridge nextaru to old Koru-Moru's manor.
1�Accept the mission?Acceptaru.Decline.
1�The School of Magic is in the Windurst Waters district, west of here. Quitarue a number of child prodigies study within the school grounds.
1�Butaru to receive the details of this mission, you'll have to speak to the teachers in the staff room there. Good luck with this mission...for our children's future.
1�Any adventarurer wants to travel around the whole world, butaru when you are asked to do itaru for your country, then it's like killing two jubjubs with one Stone spell!
1�Step inside Heavens Tower behind me and inquire ataru the Clerical Chamber to hear the full briefing of your mission. Hurry on up now!
1�Thank goodness you stopped by! You have been summoned to go inside Heavens Tower again!
1�And what's scarier still is thataru the person calling for you is none other than the Sibyl Guard Semih Lafihna, or as we at Heavens Tower call her...the defender of law and justaruice!
1�Hurry up and head inside Heavens Tower. Semih Lafihna is a busy lady, and notaru someone you wantaru to keep waiting.
1�As head of the Sibyl Guards, Semih Lafihna almostaru always carries out her investigations by herself.
1�Itaru is most unusual for her to issue a mission such as this. Itaru kind of makes you wonder whataru is going on...? But there I go saying too much again.
1�Woo-hoo...Guess who this mission is from!

1�Why, it's from the woman who has run the ladies-in-waiting with an iron fistaru for the last few decades, the oldest of the old guard, yes, it's the Star Sibyl's head lady-in-waiting, none other than Zubaba herself!
1�Anyway, she's waiting for you up in Heavens Tower's Vestal Vestibule. This is one old lady you don'taru want to keep waiting!
1�I don'taru think old Zubaba has ventured out from Heavens Tower for years now.
1�In fact, it may even be decades since she lastaru stepped out of there. Then again, Heavens Tower would never be the same withoutaru her, so I guess she feels she can'taru leave.

1�Letters with the star emblem on them like this one are the most importantaru papers issued by Heavens Tower. Usually they are only sentaru to elite people such as the ministers of the five ministries.
1�Itaru is extremely rare for a star emblem letter to be issued to a lowly adventurer such as you... Hey, don'taru tell me you're an undercover agent checking up on us or something!?
1�Itaru's a pity I cannotaru welcome you back under better circumstances. If you haven'taru heard, Windurst is now officially in a state of emergency.
1�Emergency orders have been given to all guards and adventarurers most loyal to Windurst, and the issuance of missions has been stopped pending further instructions from Heavens Tower.
1�You have some kinda business with us guards here? Then first you've gotta speak to Zokima-Rokima on the top of the steps there. He's our leader-reader!
1�A foreigner, eh?Do you have business here, or are you just a lost tourist-bourist? You're in Windurst Walls, by the way, and this is the Heavens Tower gatehouse.
1�Head west from here to go to Windurst Waters, south to go to Port Windurst, or step onto the magical blue circle-hircle at the end of the hall here to teleport inside of Heavens Tower.
1�You came to inquire about missions, huh? Then ask our guard leader-reader up there. He's certainly-mertainly a man with a mission or two.
1�It's a long and higgledy-piggledy road to get the Orastery from here. First, you have to head south past the auction house and down the road that leads to Windurst Woods.
1�Then you have to pass through to the western side of Windurst Woods and head out the exit to Port Windurst. You should be able to find the building-duilding by the shore there.
1�I'm sure you're going to get totally-rotally lost, so make sure you check your map regularly, okay!?
1�Were the Horutoto Ruins as topsy-turvy confusing for you as they are for me? No matter how many times I go there, I still manage to get lost.
1�The automaton guards, known as Cardians, are the compilation of animation magic and are really-heally a remarkable invention.
1�When they are newly created, they are just like little baby-mabies. As we teach them how to speak and how to fight, they quickly grow smarter and smarter!
1�It's only natural that we need to keep patience-matience and put forth constant effort in order to be friends with the Yagudo.
1�We're talking about a pack of beastmen. Their way of thinking is totally different from us people-beople. The first and foremost thing to strive for is to understand-ermand the other party.
1�Congratulations on advancing-mancing in rank!Say, now that you mention-bention it...just how many ranks are there? I've given up hope of further promotion so have forgotten-rotten.
1�I wonder-zonder if it is really true that all of the knowledge of Windurst is stored away in the Library of Magic?
1�I've even heard-deard that a book written by the very first Star Sibyl is still preserved as new in there!
1�There are two grades of students in the School of Magic. The exceedingly brilliant children-shildren are placed in the advanced class.
1�On the other hand, the not-so-exceedingly brilliant students-dutents are placed into the beginners class. That's just the way the world works, I guess-fess...
1�I'd like a chance to try one of these large-scale missions, but I don't really think-fink I'm up to it.

1�You see, I'm the type of Tarutaru who can't sleep on a different pillow-billow, gets seasick and airsick, and is disliked by every chocobo-kookobo he comes across. I'm just not cut out to travel-ravel.
1�The Sibyl Guards are the Mithran warrior-borriors who serve the Star Sibyl.
1�They are all so serious-zerious and strong-drong and oh so cool-looking. Why, they are once...no, twice...no, thrice more fly than the other Mithra who stray about this town!
1�When I was selected to serve as a guard in front of Heavens Tower, I was over the moon-boon! Just the thought of becoming friend-priends with all those ladies-in-waiting...Hum-hmm...
1�That dream was soon shattered-splattered when mean old Zubaba cracked down on the young ladies-in-waiting going outside. It brings tears to my eyes-cries!
1�I'm not the least bit jealous-mealous! I've delivered a document with the star emblem on it to the minister-pinister of the Orastery before.
1�I can remember I was so nervous-dervous back then. I was in a cold sweat at the thought of what punishment-bunishment would await me if I lost the darned thing.
1�No matter how you look at it, you can't help but conclude something major-dajor is going down in Heavens Tower right now.
1�The head of the Sibyl Guards, Semih Lafihna, has been going-zoing in and out of here all day. My arms are tired from giving her the Windurstian salute-dalute each time she passes by.
1�Where in Vana'diel is this Fei'Yin place-blace? Huh? Way up north past-fast the Beaucedine Glacier?
1�That still doesn't tell-jell me where it is...All I can make out is that it's going to be a really cold-old place. Better pack-zack your long johns!
1�Don't you sometimes wonder whether people and beastmen can really ever understand one another-brother?
1�The Star Sibyl thought that someday we would understand-berstand one another and tried all manner of things to work to that goal, but nothing really changed.
1�I wonder-monder if it is, as they say, set in the stars? The movement of the stars never changes-shanges, does it?
1�Whether your name goes down in the history-mistory of Windurst or not doesn't matter. What you did was indeed a great deed-yeed!
1�Thank you, adventurer-henturer!Please keep using that mighty-righty power of yours for the peace of Windurst!
1�Minister Ajido-Marujido has asked for you? My condolences.He really-deally bosses people around. The Ministers of the Orastery have always been meany-beanies.
1�Although with the members of the Mage Academy always on the front line of battle, I guess you gottaru be tough-rough or you couldn't cut it as the head honcho-poncho.
1�Even if he is Minister of the Orastery, Ajido-Marujido cannot be forgiven his transgressions. The word of Heavens Tower is the law of Windurst.

1�With Ajido-Marujido in the Dark Dungeon, who will become the next Minister of the Orastery? It will have to be a super-dooper wizard who can coordinate both the mighty-fighty War Warlocks and the Operations Division....Nobody really spring-pings to mind.
1�I havetaru clean my house, too. Adventurers have it easy, since they have moogles to look after their rooms. I'm so jealous-bealous.
1�I've heard that if adventurers put furniture in their rooms, the moogles sometimes find hidden items. Lucky-duckies!
1�Were you listening properly-doperly?You need to go ask the mission-fission details from Leepe-Hoppe on the second floor of the Rhinostery.
1�The Rhinostery probably wants you to help them with their research...They usually have their own adventurers to assist-list them though.
1�Out of the five ministries, the Aurastery issues the least mission-bissions.
1�When Professor Koru-Moru was actively performing his role as principal, there was all manner of trouble-bubbles...But these days it's been relatively quiet.
1�After the Great War twenty years ago, the Cardians started a rebellion-mellion and carried off the previous Manustery minister...
1�Following that chaos, the Manustery came to a complete standstill. Minister Apururu has worked extremely-zemely hard to get her ministry back into operation.
1�The Cardians created by the Manustery are made to act as shields for the guards. It's time we returned the favor!
1�Kupipi was saying that there is no huge-luge difference between adventurers whose names go down in history, and those who are not mentioned at all-fall.
1�The only difference-mifference between them is that the adventurers whose names go down in history are the ones that remain in people's memories.
1�...So, if it was you who we were talking about-pout, you would sorta be remembered. Vaguely.

1�According to the gossip-dossip of the ladies-in-waiting, Semih Lafihna has been to-ing and fro-ing all over the place trying to find information on the bearer of darkness that appeared in Heavens Tower.
1�I was standing rightaru here when all the fuss erupted, and I have no memory-zemory of letting such a creature pass into the tower. It must be some sort of ghosty-toasty...
1�You gotta hand it to those Mithra. She goes off in search of the thing when most normal people would be running in the other direction. Ghosties give me the shivers...
1�I heard from the ladies-in-waiting that they haven't seen the Star Sibyl around lately-dately.
1�You know, with Ajido-Marujido forgiven for his crimes and we guards going unpunished-bunished, I get the feeling that something more importantaru must be going on...
1�Maybe, just maybe... She's taking a secretaru vacation!? Hmm, not likely, huh...?
1�Hooray! I never thought that Minister Ajido-Marujido would be forgiven so quickly-trickly for his transgressions!
1�Were you there when he talked with the Star Sibyl? I heard that Minister Apururu said she has a lot to thank you for!
1�Lady Zubaba is being all naggy-haggy about the guards helping out with the Dark Dungeon jailbreak.
1�As soon as she has any free time on her hands, she uses it to picky-stick on other people's faults. I knew it was too good to lastaru...
1�Help!I don't wantaruy be eaten by this angry Mithra womany! Please protectaruy me!
1�Gee...why didn'taruy they let me give you the mission briefingy? I'm sick of serving as the punching bag for this angry Mithra and her list of complaintaruys.
1�Somebody please do somethingy. I'm notaruy supposed to be the complaints desk, I'm supposed to be a hip and happening guardy!
1�Windurst Walls is the scariestaruy district of Windurstaruy. Mainly because it is filled with Mithra like this oney.
1�Ooopsy! I'm sorry!I didn'taruy mean to speak ill of the Mithra! Nice lady! Don'taruy bite me, lady!
1�Oh, greataruy! Now this Mithra woman is angry over the mission you were just assignedy.
1�Yes, we are providing notaruy only food, but weapons and armor, to the Yagudo. But such is the price of peacey.
1�You were promotarued to rank two?Boy, thataruy was quicky! Before I know it, you'll be a higher rank than me.
1�The books and scrolls made in Windurstaruy look justaruy like ordinary books and scrolls do. But what's inside is totally differentaruy!
1�It's kind of like the wands in the Mage Academy, in thataruy those library books are dangerous things to play withy. You simply don'taruy know what bizarre enchantment has been placed on themy.
1�Did you know thataruy the Principal of the School of Magic is the renowned Professor Koru-Moru?
1�Years ago, the person Professor Koru-Moru appointarued as his successor to become principal ran away. What an awkward position that put him iny.
1�Have you ever had the chance to talk to Ms. Kupipi up in the Clerical Chamber of Heavens Taruwer?
1�She may not look itaruy, but she has quite a noggin on her. Why, she's memorized all the names and faces of every guard and adventarurer in the whole of Windurstaruy!
1�Whenever you mention the Sibyl Guards to the other Mithra in this town, they screw their faces up into feline frowns.
1�Don'taruy ask me why... You'll have to find out for yourselfy. Just don'taruy ask that Mithra woman therey. She'll scratch your eyes out with her tempery!
1�Zubaba's been running things in Heavens Taruwer since the currentaruy Star Sibyl was a child...which makes her pretty old when you think aboutaruy ity!
1�It's a wonder she hasn'taruy become bored, locking herself up inside Heavens Taruwer for all that timey. I'm surprised she hasn'taruy turned into a mushroom by nowy!
1�The entrance to Heavens Taruwer is justaruy therey. Don'taruy stand out here wondering what to do. Hurry up and go insidey!
1�When you're up there in the Planetarium, could you please-blease make a wish for the peace of Windurstaruy?
1�The Minister of the Rhinostery, Ms. Rukususu, has come back to Windurstaruy.
1�Although she's been in the arctic for such a long time, she was still as beautaruful as every. Oh, gosh! I think I'm falling for hery...
1�I just overheard a littarul from the people coming out of Heavens Taruwer.
1�Sounds as if the very importarunt talisman that sealed away the spooky old lord of the beastmen has been stolen! Don'taruy tell me... You're being sent to retrieve it, rightaruy?
1�It seems thataruy the meeting of the five ministries ended all too soony.
1�Professor Koru-Moru turned up on time for once, and Minister Ajido-Marujido didn't even complainy! It was too quietaruy. I don'taruy like ity!
1�The ministaru of the Rhinostery, Ms. Rukususu, came out of Heavens Tower with the mostaruy cheerful look on her facey.
1�Now my heart, too, is as brightaruy and cheerful as Windurstaruy isy. There isn't a cloud in sightaruy nowy!
1�Minister Ajido-Marujido is notaruy as popular with the more hot-blooded Mithra as you would thinky.
1�The D-Dark D-Dungeon!Brrr, brrr, brrr!
1�I would rather becomey a guard in Windurst Woods than be throwny in there!
1�Have you heardy of the great genius Karaha-Baruha? Karaha-Baruha was the previous Minister of the Optistery.
1�In the northy of Windurst Walls you can find the House of the Hero. That is where the Ministers of the Optistery livey when they retirey. It's where Karaha-Baruha would have been livingy...
1�Speaking of the Rhinostery, how's Miss Kerutoto?
1�From the time she was a tiny Tarutaru, Kerutoto would come outy with the most frighteningy things all of a sudden. Such a strange little poppet.
1�I never went to schooly. But with all my intense training-waining, I've become a top-notchy guard.
1�I've even made friends with this Mithra lady-wady. All as a result of my hard worky and discipline!
1�Our biggest worry was Captain Rakoh Buuma in Windurst Woods. Being a Mithra, I didn'taru think she would understandy our desirey to help Minister Apururu.
1�But she was all for it! Now I think Mithra are the cat's pajamas!
1�This is justaruy between you and me, but...I saw an adventurer passing throughy the Priming Gate here in Windurst Walls.
1�The Cardian guard justaruy let him throughy without a wordy. I guess thataruy means he had permission from Heavens Tower.I don'taruy really know, thoughy.
1�I've heardy some disturbing rumors. Apparently Doctor Shantotto has been trying all sorts of things to rousey Ajido-Marujido from his slumbery...

1�The poor minister is probably in much more danger now than when he was languishingy in the Dark Dungeon... I'm terribly-werribly worried for him, but I'm petrifiedy of what I might see if I go to check!
1�Oh, good griefy, the Mithra are getting all firedy up again. You can'taru mentiony the word ??Yagudo?? around them without sparks flying out of their ears!
1�The Orastery mages are relievedy that Minister Ajido-Marujido will be back to run the ministry just as he always has.
1�The boys in Operations were so afraidy that Doctor Shantotto would returny as minister, they started planning out Code E emergency procedures...Ahahaha......What? You think they were serious?
1�Oh,  ! I heardy you were the one who saved the Star Sibyl!
1�Can I have your autography? It'll become a family heirloom! I'll keepy it locked in a treasure chest!
1�What's that you said?Don't you darrre rrrepeat that!
1�Don't you dare tell me you agrrreed to that mission of carrying offerrrings to the beastmen in Giddeus!?
1�Grrr... And you think I'm going to stand by and let you do that without giving you a piece of my mind!?
1�I don't give a damn whetherrr you went up to rrrank two or not.
1�I only wish you'd hurry up and make these slackerrrs underrrstand just how overrrly apathetic and laid-back Windurst has become.
1�A-hah!? Magic books, eh?I once hearrrd from someone that there was an uproarrr when a magic book fell into the hands of the Yagudo.
1�But that's beside the point.For crrrying out loud...would you shorrrties get out of my way and let me meet the Starrr Sibyl?
1�If you have enough time on yourrr hands to do that silly mission, why don't you lend us Mithra a hand forrr a change?
1�Oh, come on. Give me a brrreak! Grrr...I've had it with these guarrrds!
1�Hey!Just wherrre are you heading now?
1�Well, when you speak to the Tarutaru inside of herrre, tell them to go see forrr themselves just how equipped otherrr countries are to fight off the beastmen.
1�I hearrrd that!You'rrre talking about the Sibyl Guards, rrright?
1�They'rrre no Mithra, that mob. They werrre rrraised by the Tarutaru, so they have lost theirrr Mithran spirit! Why, they'rrre nothing more than a band of traitorrrs!
1�What's all the rrruckus about? Has something happened in Heavens Towerrr?
1�I came herrre to give that Star Sibyl a piece of my mind! Why do we have to be frrriends with those filthy Yagudo?
1�They continue rrravaging the countryside just because no one herrre in Windurst has the guts to stand up to them!
1�Ajido-Marujido? Yeah, I know him. He's the one that's always looking for Nanaa Mihgo.
1�I don't want anything to do with lowlives who willingly deal with the Cat Burrrglar.
1�What did you just say?You wanna try rrrepeating that?
1�I was told a lot of stories about the Grrreat War as a child, but only those that centered on Chieftainness Perih Vashai.
1�Although I did hear a story that Windurst was saved by a grrreat light that flowed out from the magic towers. I wonder what could've caused that light?
1�The Rhinostery? They have a long history with the Mithra.
1�Didn't you know?The first Tarutaru to visit us in our southern homeland were researchers from the Rhinostery.
1�I've just given in.Every time I talk to these little Tarutaru, I just can't seem to keep the edge on my words. I've lost my bite completely.
1�Maybe I need to focus myself and rrredo my basic training...
1�I don't want to burst their bubble, but I think the reason Captain Buuma is helping the Tarutaru is because she wants to tick off the Sibyl Guards.
1�I've been thinking that the Star Sibyl must have some kind of strrrategy in mind for dealing with those treacherous Yagudo.
1�This whole ??Okay, here's your tribute!?? facade is just a stalling tactic. Or at least, that's what I'd like to think.
1�You know, I've been thinking. If the Sibyl Guards are orrrphans of the Great War, then wouldn't they hate the Yagudo even more than us other Mithra?
1�I suppose that as a race, the Mithra don't hold much with grrrudges. Maybe their anger has cooled off over the years?
1�Those black-blooded, back-stabbing Yagudo scum! We Mithra should wipe out the entire rrrace!
1�What is the Star Sibyl afrrraid of? Taking rrresponsiblity for a war? That Windurst would lose?
1�If fighting brrreaks out on the streets like it did twenty years ago, we should just blast the hell out of 'em with that summoning magic stuff.
1�Chieftainness Perih Vashai is to seek an audience with the Star Sibyl concerning the events surrounding Orastery minister Ajido-Marujido.

1�Don't get me wrong--it's not like the chieftainness is a close friend of the minister or anything. These events have set something in motion. And I think we're about to find out what that something is...
1�We Mithra are going to be rrrunning wild in Windurst Woods again, so don't forget to stop by. Oh, and before you go...
1�...can I have your autograph?
1�Seek and gather...
1�...the seven colors...
1�...that cover the sky...
1�...and embrace the earth...
1�Anything in your grubby hands?Maybe...Just dirt.
1�Seek and gather...
1�...the seven colors...
1�...that cover the sky...
1�...and embrace the earth...
1�The voice from the #???? rings in your head.
1�...Seek and gather...the seven colors...that cover the sky...and embrace the earth...
1�You give the 3???? to Joker.
1�Accept the offer?When you put it that way...The hammer or the axe?
1�A blue energy wells up within you..
1�A blue energy wells up within you..
1�You remember the voice of Carbuncle.
1�This is no Book of the Gods. It's just a work of the famous Karaha-Baruha...
